accessibility.text: To shift left, a number is added to x before squaring
For example, x2 shifted 6 left is (x+6)2 and 2x2+8x shifted 2 left is 2(x+2)2+8x

This works because it effectively shifts the x values going into the function. If you are adding 1 to x, it makes an x value of -1 produce the x value normally produced by 0, moving it 1 to the left. See the tables on the next slide for more information.
